Q : what is concurrency and multithreading? 
🔁Concurrency – Big Concept

Concurrency means doing multiple tasks at the same time (or overlapping).

It’s about managing many tasks together so they make progress.

You can achieve concurrency in many ways — one of them is multithreading.

🧵 Multithreading – One Way to Achieve Concurrency

Multithreading means using multiple threads inside a program so that tasks can run concurrently.

Each thread runs independently, so multiple parts of your code can execute simultaneously.

💡 Example:
Imagine you have 3 tasks: A, B, C

Concurrency: You try to handle A, B, C together (maybe by switching quickly).

Multithreading: You create 3 threads — one for A, one for B, one for C — to run them together.

✅ In short (for interview):
“Concurrency is a concept of doing multiple tasks at the same time or overlapping in time. Multithreading is one way to 
achieve concurrency — by using multiple threads to run parts of a program simultaneously.”

