How internally multithreading works?

Suppose in a thread pool (Executors) there are 10 threads and only 1 task is given.

- One thread will pick and execute that task.
- Remaining 9 threads will stay idle/waiting.
- When new tasks come, other free threads can pick those tasks and execute them.
- After completing the task, the thread goes back to the thread pool and becomes available for reuse.

This improves performance because threads are reused instead of creating new threads again and again.

